7. Duplicate or Multiple Member Accounts
7.1.
You are only allowed to open and use one (1) Member Account with the Operator on the Website. If You open or attempt to open more than one (1) Member Account on the same Website, for whatever reason, or if you have placed a number of bets from duplicate or multiple accounts which You have opened irregularly, the Operator reserves the right to block You or close any or all of Your Member Accounts at its discretion, and all bets will be considered null and void. The Operator also reserves the right to withhold any deposits or winnings upon the discovery of duplicate or multiple Member Accounts being opened or used by You, at its sole discretion. The Operator retains the right to take further action against You as deemed necessary.
7.2.
If You notice that You have more than one (1) Member Account under different names, You must notify the Operator immediately.
7.3.
Should the Operator decide to allow You to keep one (1) Member Account, it will be at the sole discretion of the Operator to establish which shall be Your remaining  Member Account. The Operator will deduct an administrative fee of 10% (of deposits set at a minimum of €30 (in words: thirty euros) or equivalent) for every Member Account You have opened as well as any other deductions that may apply in accordance with these T&Cs.
7.4.
Furthermore, if You attempt to open any additional, duplicate or multiple Member Accounts after Your original Member Account has been closed due to gambling addiction, any funds held in Your additional Member Account/s will be immediately forfeited and retained and no winnings shall be paid out to You under any circumstance.
