11. Member Account Administration
11.1.
Any deposit You make into Your Member Account will be held for Your use until You place a bid for a bet, or accept a bet on the Website. The Operator will then hold such amount awaiting the outcome of the bet.
11.2.
The amount You have staked which represents Your current exposure at any time is referred to as the “
Total Bet
”, or any other equivalent term as described in the Game and/or Game Rules from time to time.  The total balance in Your Member Account, less the Total Bet, is the remaining amount of money in Your Member Account which has not yet been used for a bet and is referred to as Your
"Available to Bet"
balance. This will determine Your betting limit.
11.3.
The Operator will calculate Your Available to Bet balance, from time to time, as well as settling other bets made by You with other users through Your participation in the Games.
11.4.
The Operator's calculations of Your Reserved Amount, Your Available to Bet balance and any amounts owed by You in terms of these T&Cs will be final and, in the absence of any manifest error, will not be subject to any enquiry, challenge or investigation.
11.5.
The Operator will both on a market basis and in general set off any losses against any gains made to Your balance.
11.6.
When You have matched a bet on the  Website, the Operator will hold the amount staked awaiting the outcome of the event, and declare a winner. At this point the bet is binding and cannot be cancelled or withdrawn. Nor can any amount held by the Operator in this respect be withdrawn.
11.7.
You may participate in a Game only if You have sufficient funds on Your Member Account for such participation. The Operator does not grant any credit for the use of its services and will not give You any credit for participation in any Game.
11.8.
Information required to deposit funds into Your Member Account, can be found under “My Account” and “Deposit” pages of the Website. You can use any of the methods available to You as specified on these pages as may be amended from time to time. Please note that some of the methods may not be available in some jurisdictions.
11.9.
Depending on the method selected for deposits, such deposits can incur charges. For current fees regarding depositing funds, see "My Account" and "Deposit" for each deposit method. Your bank or other payment service provider may independently charge You for bank wire transfers and other methods of payment.
11.10.
The Operator accepts payments made in several currencies. Please note that any potential exchange premiums or charges are payable by You.
11.11.
When using a credit or debit card for depositing funds, Your funds only clear when the Operator has received an irrevocable approval and authorisation code. Should the Operator not receive such approval and code Your Member Account will not be credited with those funds.
11.12.
The Operator reserves the right to use additional procedures and means to verify Your identity when effecting deposits into Your Member Account.
11.13.
You shall not treat the Operator as a financial institution. Credit balances in Your Member Account will not bear interest.
12. General rules for participating in Games
12.1.
You can only place a bet on the Website and Games after opening a Member Account and depositing sufficient funds in Your Member Account.
12.2.
The Operator retains the right, at its absolute discretion, to stop offering any of its Games at any point. Any money staked or bets placed on such Game will be refunded back to You by the Operator.
12.3.
Any bet You place on the Website and Games will be governed by the version of these T&Cs and Game Rules valid at the time of the bet’s acceptance.
12.4.
A bet is deemed to have been accepted as soon as it is received on the Operator’s system, validated and processed. Confirmation is then sent to Your device or computer with a unique number and/or time stamp.
12.5.
The Operator retains the absolute right and discretion to decline to accept bets on any Game without providing any reason.
12.6.
The list of all the bets You place and the respective details are available to You on Your Member Account.
12.7.
Should the Operator decide to close Your account for any reason as explained in these T&Cs,  bets which have already been placed will not be voided and You will be paid any winnings and/or unwagered deposits, unless there is reasonable suspicion of fraudulent activity.
12.8.
A bet which You place and confirm, cannot be amended, withdrawn or cancelled for any reason.
12.9.
When You place a bet on the Website and Games, You acknowledge that You have read, understood and agree to these T&Cs and Game Rules.
12.10.
Winnings will be paid into Your Member Account after the final result is confirmed. However, and without prejudice to any other clause within these T&Cs, the Operator reserves the right to forfeit and withhold any winnings should there be investigations into the result of an event resulting from a suspicion of criminal activities that may have affected the result of the event. If the irregularity is confirmed, then the Operator retains the right to void any related bets and resultant winnings if any.
12.11.
If bets, which exceed any stipulated limits, are erroneously accepted by the Operator, the excess amount will be disregarded, and the bet amount placed will be revised accordingly and the difference paid back to the party and counterparty of the bet.
12.12.
Communication errors do occasionally happen. Bets are confirmed only when received on the Operator’s servers in Malta. Should there be a break in communication after You offer a bet, and such bet is received by the Operator’s servers prior to the communication break, such bet will still be considered valid. You will be informed that Your bet has been accepted once communication is re-established at which time the bet may have been already utilised. You will receive information about the outcome of the bet placed. If the bet offer is not received at the Operator servers then it will not stand, and the bet amount will not have been taken from Your Member Account.
12.13.
If a Game is started but fails or produces an inexact result due to a breakdown of the Game account management software and/or of the Game and/or of the random number generator, all the stakes and wins coming from that Game will be cancelled and the Game account balance will be restored to its position prior to the start of the Game. In this case the funds You bet will be returned to Your Member Account.
12.14.
If You disconnect Your session with the Operator during an active Game, the amount of funds You will have staked will be returned to Your Member Account. When applicable, amounts of un-wagered stakes will be returned to Your Member Account and confirmed bets will be processed and winnings will be credited to Your Member Account, if any.
12.15.
The Operator endeavours to make no mistakes when quoting paytables; if any mistake is inadvertently made, the Operator reserves the right to modify the payout ratios even once the event has finished (when applicable).
12.16.
In the event of software or RNG malfunctioning, the bet will be considered null and void and the amount of the stake will be returned to You.
12.17.
The Operator reserves the right to change the prize of a promotion if it cannot be delivered due to unforeseen circumstances or force majeure. In this case, the Operator shall ensure that the You are placed in at least the same, if not better, position.
13. Payouts
13.1.
When the outcome of a Game You participate in is determined or, where applicable, the Operator has confirmed the relevant result of an event and settled the markets, all winnings will be available for use in Your Member Account.
13.2.
If the Operator mistakenly credits Your Member Account with winnings that do not belong to You, whether due to a technical or human error or otherwise, You are obliged to notify the Operator immediately by email. Such amount will remain the property of the Operator and the amount will be transferred from Your Member Account back to the Operator. If You withdraw the funds erroneously transferred to You before the Operator becomes aware of such error, the amount erroneously paid will constitute a civil debt owed by You to the Operator in terms of applicable law.
13.3.
The Operator reserves the right to carry out additional verification procedures at any time.
