14.4.
Should You use bonus funds given by the Operator in breach of any Bonus Rules or to play on Games which are not included in the list of Games that count towards meeting such bonus requirements as indicated in such Bonus Rules, then the Operator reserves the right to refuse withdrawals, confiscate bonus money and/or winnings without notice, and to freeze, suspend or close Your Member Account without prior warning.
15. Cancellation of Bets
15.1.
The Operator products are consumed instantly when playing and therefore the Operator does not accept requests for cancellations of bets or stakes or refunds when You are playing. If You play a Game with real money, the money will be drawn from Your Member Account instantly.
16. Withdrawals from Your Member Account
16.1.
You may withdraw any amount up to the “Available to Withdraw” balance in Your Operator’s Member Account by issuing the Operator with a valid notice of withdrawal on the Website.
16.2.
To free Your Member Account balance and withdraw all Your funds, You must first cancel any bets or actions which remain outstanding.
16.3.
Notices for withdrawals must be made via the Website. The Operator will not accept requests for withdrawal made by telephone or electronic mail and the Operator’s employees are not permitted to circumvent these instructions.
16.4.
Assuming that You have submitted your verifiable identification documents (if applicable), the Operator will strive to process Your withdrawal request within twenty-four (24) hours. There could be instances where this may not be possible, due to high withdrawal volumes. However, in all cases, we will process your withdrawal request within five (5) working days, as required by our license.
16.5.
The Operator will credit Your Member Account back using the same method used to deposit funds in the Member Account, whenever this is possible. Upon withdrawing funds, Your own bank or other payment provider may add a further handling charge which may vary over time and for which You remain responsible.
16.6.
The Operator may request verifiable identification documents before processing withdrawal requests and also reserves the right to review Your Website/Game usage to detect any irregular or fraudulent playing patterns.
16.7.
Irregular or fraudulent player practices include, without limitation, the following, and shall be considered as such for bonus play-through requirement purposes:
a)
Equal, zero or low margin bets or hedge betting;
b)
Placing single bets equal to or in excess of 30% or more of the value of Your total balance (including any given bonus) until such time as the wagering requirements for that bonus have been met.
c)
Bets placed through duplicate or multiple accounts belonging to the same user.
16.8.
Should the Operator deem that irregular playing practices have occurred, the Operator reserves the right to withhold any withdrawals and/or winnings and to confiscate all winnings and bonuses obtained through such playing practices.
16.9.
In the case of withdrawal requests pertaining to funds which have never been used for wagering, the Operator will only remit Your funds when the extended due diligence procedure has been successfully carried out. The Operator reserves the right to apply a 5% charge on withdrawals of a minimum amount of €10 (in words: ten euros) or equivalent, if such amount has not been used at least once for gambling on the Website.
17. Closing Your Member Account
17.1.
If You would like to close Your account, You must send an email notifying the Operator on the Customer Support Contact as indicated in these T&Cs. The remaining balance in Your Member Account will be transferred back to You once Your identity is verified and any documents requested are submitted.
17.2.
The method of repayment will be at the Operator's absolute discretion.
17.3.
The Operator reserves the right to close Your Member Account and to refund You the available balance, subject to the deduction of relevant withdrawal charges, at the Operator’s absolute discretion and without any obligation to state a reason or give prior notice.
18. Inactive Member Account
18.1.
Your Member Account shall be deemed inactive if it has not been accessed for twelve (12) months and has a real money balance.
18.2.
The Operator shall notify You at least thirty (30) days before Your Member Account is due to become inactive. In such case You will have the option to withdraw Your funds, subject to any procedures for withdrawal set out herein and in accordance with laws and regulations.
18.3.
Where Your Member Account becomes inactive, the Operator may elect to charge a fee for inactivity or to close Your Member Account. Fees may only be charged to an inactive Member Account as long as that Member Account does not go into a negative balance.
18.4.
Where the Operator elects to charge an inactivity fee, such fee shall be a monthly administrative fee of €5 (in words: five euros) or the equivalent in any other currency.
18.5.
Where the Operator elects to close Your Member Account, the Operator shall, without prejudice to any AML legislation, endeavour to refund Your remaining balance, by remitting the funds directly or by contacting You using the information at the Operator’s disposal.
18.6.
If the Operator is unsuccessful in remitting the remaining balance, Your Member Account will (i) either be left open or (ii) will be closed and the remaining balance will be appropriated by the Operator.
18.7.
Where the remaining balance is appropriated, acquisitive prescription shall apply in favour of the Operator where the following conditions are satisfied:-
a)
After failing to remit the funds the Operator shall send You a final notice informing You that the funds shall be appropriated if You do not provide a means for the funds to be remitted within a specified timeframe;
b)
Such notice shall be sent to You through every means of communication available to the Operator, including by post;
c)
The Operator may allocate the remaining funds in its favour after the lapse of 5 (in words: five) years from when the final notice has been sent to You;
Any player funds appropriated by the Operator shall be used to fund responsible gaming endeavours.
19. Responsible Gaming
19.1.
You may at Your own discretion choose to self-exclude Yourself from playing any Games on the Website (for a definite or an indefinite period of time or permanently). In order to block Your Member Account You need to go to Your Member Account profile and choose “Self-Exclusion” and complete the form or contact the Operator on the Customer Support Contact.
19.2.
Should you wish to reopen your Member Account during a definite exclusion, you will be able to do so following a 1 (one) day cool-off period before You may resume to use the Games and Website. Should you wish to reopen your account during an indefinite exclusion, you will be able to do so following a 7 (seven) day cool-off period before You may resume to use the Games and Website. In both cases, you are required to contact the Operator on our Customer Support Contact to make the request. A permanently excluded account cannot be reopened. Once Your Member Account is re-opened in accordance with the procedure described herein, You shall be responsible for any losses that ensue thereafter as a result of Your continued use of Your Member Account and shall in no case be refunded by the Operator. No Member Accounts may be reopened or reactivated in cases of permanent exclusions or exclusions for the reason of gambling addiction.
19.3.
You may also choose to impose a responsible gaming limit (deposit limit / wager limit / loss limit / time per session limit) on a daily/weekly/monthly basis, on Your Member Account. A day starts at 00:00 UTC and ends at 23.59 UTC. A calendar week begins at 00.00 UTC every Monday morning and runs until 23.59 UTC on the Sunday of that given week. A month starts at 00.00 UTC on the 1st and will run until 23.59 UTC on the last day of the month (28/29th, 30th or 31st).
19.4.
In order to set a responsible gaming limit, You must log in to Your  Member Account and set or manage Your responsible gaming limits on Your Member Account. If You decide to impose stricter limits, this update will occur immediately. If you choose to increase your limits (make them more lenient) this update will occur following a 1 (one) day cool-off period. Any gaming limit You choose to impose on Your Member Account on the Website will not be applied across Your other (if any) Member Accounts opened on the other different branded websites owned by LeoVegas Mobile Gaming Group, and will apply solely to the Member Account of this Website.
19.5.
Member Accounts closed for gambling addiction reasons shall be closed for a minimum of 5 (five) years and may only be reopened or re-activated when You make a positive request to the Operator for Your account to be reopened after the 5 (five) year period has elapsed. Should You not make such a request Your account shall remain closed. For the avoidance of doubt, the Operator shall not give a 24hr (twenty-four hours) cool-off period for time-outs, and hence in this case, Your Member Account shall re-open automatically once the selected period has expired.
19.6.
Should you wish to withdraw any of Your remaining funds during the period of self-exclusion, you may contact the Operator on the Customer Support Contact.
20. Fraud and Anti-Money Laundering
20.1.
All transactions will be checked by the Operator’s personnel in accordance with the prevention of money laundering laws and regulations as applicable from time to time.
20.2.
Any suspicious activity on Your Member Account could lead You to being reported to the relevant authorities and to the consequential freezing of Your funds. The Operator also reserves the right to suspend or close Your Member Account and confiscate Your funds in case of any suspicious fraudulent or illegal activity.
